SIMPLE: sessile
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sessile
<hw>Ses"sile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sessilis</ets> low, dwarf, from <ets>sedere</ets>,
<ets>sessum</ets>, to sit: cf. F. <ets>sessile</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Attached without any sensible projecting support.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Resting directly upon the main
stem or branch, without a petiole or footstalk; <as>as, a
<ex>sessile</ex> leaf or blossom</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Permanently attached; -- said of
the gonophores of certain hydroids which never became
detached.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sessile-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
